<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1518] NetworkConnector is leaking a thread if broker disconnects</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1518</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following scenario: Two brokers A and B. Broker B sets up a NetworkConnector to Broker A using a static URL list and setting duplex =&quot;true&quot; (see attached configuration). At runtime Broker B will correctly connect to Broker A. jconsole shows a NetworkBridge being set up.&lt;br/&gt;
For every network bridge that gets set up, three threads get started in Broker A, e.g:&lt;br/&gt;
VMTransport: vm://localhost#5&lt;br/&gt;
ActiveMQ Transport: tcp://host:4533&lt;br/&gt;
ActiveMQ Connection Dispatcher: /host:4533&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, when Broker B disconnects, the network bridge will be closed down and the above threads need to cleaned up. The first two threads do get closed correctly, however the Connection Dispatcher thread stays alive and does not get closed. We are leaking this thread!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;use MessageBroker 5.0.0.5, Windows, using NetworkConnector with duplex set to true&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
